-- Moscow Exchange May Start Foreign Stock Futures Trading in 2013
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-10-11T17:11:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-11/moscow-exchange-may-start-foreign-stock-futures-trading-in-2013.html
The Moscow Exchange may start
trading foreign stock futures next year and is planning to
expand foreign currency futures trading.  “Right now the Moscow Exchange is developing the
parameters for trading foreign stock futures,” Roman Sulzhik,
managing director of Moscow Exchange’s derivatives market said
by e-mail today. “The launch decision may be taken in early
2013.”  Following the decision, the futures would start trading in
2013, Nikita Bekasov, the exchange’s spokesman, said by phone.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ksenia Galouchko in Moscow at 
